spoonacular API

API and SDK Documentation

Version: 1.0

The spoonacular Nutrition, Recipe, and Food API allows you to access over 380,000 recipes, thousands of ingredients, 800,000 food products, and 100,000 menu items. Our food ontology and semantic recipe search engine makes it possible to search for recipes using natural language queries, such as "gluten free brownies without sugar" or "low fat vegan cupcakes." You can automatically calculate the nutritional information for any recipe, analyze recipe costs, visualize ingredient lists, find recipes for what's in your fridge, find recipes based on special diets, nutritional requirements, or favorite ingredients, classify recipes into types and cuisines, convert ingredient amounts, or even compute an entire meal plan. With our powerful API, you can create many kinds of food and especially nutrition apps.

Special diets/dietary requirements currently available include: vegan, vegetarian, pescetarian, gluten free, grain free, dairy free, high protein, whole 30, low sodium, low carb, Paleo, ketogenic, FODMAP, and Primal.

Ingredients

autocompleteIngredientSearch

Autocomplete Ingredient Search

Autocomplete the entry of an ingredient.


/food/ingredients/autocomplete

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Android

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;

import java.util.*;

public class IngredientsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        IngredientsApi apiInstance = new IngredientsApi();
        String query = query_example; // String | The (natural language) search query.
        Integer number = 56; // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
        Boolean metaInformation = true; // Boolean | Whether to return more meta information about the ingredients.
        String intolerances = intolerances_example; // String | A comma-separated list of intolerances. All recipes returned must not contain ingredients that are not suitable for people with the intolerances entered. See a full list of supported intolerances.
        try {
            array[inline_response_200_25] result = apiInstance.autocompleteIngredientSearch(query, number, metaInformation, intolerances);
            System.out.println(result);

    }
}

//apiKeyScheme.apiKeyPrefix['apiKey'] = "Token"

var opts = { 
  'query': query_example, // {{String}} The (natural language) search query.
  'number': 56, // {{Integer}} The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
  'metaInformation': true, // {{Boolean}} Whether to return more meta information about the ingredients.
  'intolerances': intolerances_example // {{String}} A comma-separated list of intolerances. All recipes returned must not contain ingredients that are not suitable for people with the intolerances entered. See a full list of supported intolerances.
};
var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.autocompleteIngredientSearch(opts, callback);

computeIngredientAmount

Compute Ingredient Amount

Compute the amount you need of a certain ingredient for a certain nutritional goal. For example, how much pineapple do you have to eat to get 10 grams of protein?


/food/ingredients/{id}/amount

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"https://api.spoonacular.com/food/ingredients/{id}/amount?nutrient=&target=&unit="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.IngredientsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class IngredientsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        IngredientsApi apiInstance = new IngredientsApi();
        BigDecimal id = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The id of the ingredient you want the amount for.
        String nutrient = nutrient_example; // String | The target nutrient. See a list of supported nutrients.
        BigDecimal target = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The target number of the given nutrient.
        String unit = unit_example; // String | The target unit.
        try {
            inline_response_200_23 result = apiInstance.computeIngredientAmount(id, nutrient, target, unit);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling IngredientsApi#computeIngredientAmount");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

getIngredientInformation

Get Ingredient Information

Use an ingredient id to get all available information about an ingredient, such as its image and supermarket aisle.


/food/ingredients/{id}/information

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"https://api.spoonacular.com/food/ingredients/{id}/information?amount=&unit="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.IngredientsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class IngredientsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        IngredientsApi apiInstance = new IngredientsApi();
        Integer id = 56; // Integer | The item's id.
        BigDecimal amount = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The amount of this ingredient.
        String unit = unit_example; // String | The unit for the given amount.

        IngredientsApi apiInstance = new IngredientsApi();
        String query = query_example; // String | The (natural language) search query.
        Boolean addChildren = true; // Boolean | Whether to add children of found foods.
        BigDecimal minProteinPercent = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum percentage of protein the food must have (between 0 and 100).
        BigDecimal maxProteinPercent = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum percentage of protein the food can have (between 0 and 100).
        BigDecimal minFatPercent = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum percentage of fat the food must have (between 0 and 100).
        BigDecimal maxFatPercent = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum percentage of fat the food can have (between 0 and 100).
        BigDecimal minCarbsPercent = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum percentage of carbs the food must have (between 0 and 100).
        BigDecimal maxCarbsPercent = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum percentage of carbs the food can have (between 0 and 100).
        Boolean metaInformation = true; // Boolean | Whether to return more meta information about the ingredients.
        String intolerances = intolerances_example; // String | A comma-separated list of intolerances. All recipes returned must not contain ingredients that are not suitable for people with the intolerances entered. See a full list of supported intolerances.
        String sort = sort_example; // String | The strategy to sort recipes by. See a full list of supported sorting options.
        String sortDirection = sortDirection_example; // String | The direction in which to sort. Must be either 'asc' (ascending) or 'desc' (descending).
        Integer offset = 56; // Integer | The number of results to skip (between 0 and 900).
        Integer number = 56; // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
        try {
            inline_response_200_26 result = apiInstance.ingredientSearch(query, addChildren, minProteinPercent, maxProteinPercent, minFatPercent, maxFatPercent, minCarbsPercent, maxCarbsPercent, metaInformation, intolerances, sort, sortDirection, offset, number);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling IngredientsApi#ingredientSearch");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Delete an item from the user's meal plan.


/mealplanner/{username}/items/{id}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.MealPlanningApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class MealPlanningApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        MealPlanningApi apiInstance = new MealPlanningApi();
        Items_id_body body = ; // Items_id_body | 
        String hash = hash_example; // String | The private hash for the username.
        String username = username_example; // String | The username.
        BigDecimal id = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The shopping list item id.
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.deleteFromMealPlan(body, hash, username, id);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling MealPlanningApi#deleteFromMealPlan");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

{
    public class deleteFromMealPlanExample
    {
        public void main()
        {

            // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
            Configuration.Default.ApiKey.Add("apiKey", "YOUR_API_KEY");
            // Uncomment below to setup prefix (e.g. Bearer) for API key, if needed
            // Configuration.Default.ApiKeyPrefix.Add("apiKey", "Bearer");

            var apiInstance = new MealPlanningApi();
            var body = new Items_id_body(); // Items_id_body | 
            var hash = hash_example;  // String | The private hash for the username.
            var username = username_example;  // String | The username.
            var id = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | The shopping list item id.

            try
            {
                // Delete from Meal Plan
                Object result = apiInstance.deleteFromMealPlan(body, hash, username, id);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling MealPlanningApi.deleteFromMealPlan: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

deleteFromShoppingList

Delete from Shopping List

Delete an item from the current shopping list of the user.


/mealplanner/{username}/shopping-list/items/{id}

public class MealPlanningApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        MealPlanningApi apiInstance = new MealPlanningApi();
        Items_id_body_1 body = ; // Items_id_body_1 | 
        String hash = hash_example; // String | The private hash for the username.
        String username = username_example; // String | The username.
        Integer id = 56; // Integer | The item's id.
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.deleteFromShoppingList(body, hash, username, id);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling MealPlanningApi#deleteFromShoppingList");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

generateMealPlan

Generate Meal Plan

Generate a meal plan with three meals per day (breakfast, lunch, and dinner).


/mealplanner/generate

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"https://api.spoonacular.com/mealplanner/generate?timeFrame=&targetCalories=&diet=&exclude="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.MealPlanningApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class MealPlanningApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        MealPlanningApi apiInstance = new MealPlanningApi();
        String timeFrame = timeFrame_example; // String | Either for one "day" or an entire "week".
        BigDecimal targetCalories = 1.2; // BigDecimal | What is the caloric target for one day? The meal plan generator will try to get as close as possible to that goal.
        String diet = diet_example; // String | Enter a diet that the meal plan has to adhere to. See a full list of supported diets.
        String exclude = exclude_example; // String | A comma-separated list of allergens or ingredients that must be excluded.
        try {
            inline_response_200_40 result = apiInstance.generateMealPlan(timeFrame, targetCalories, diet, exclude);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling MealPlanningApi#generateMealPlan");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

        String diet = diet_example; // String | Enter a diet that the meal plan has to adhere to. See a full list of supported diets.
        String exclude = exclude_example; // String | A comma-separated list of allergens or ingredients that must be excluded.

BigDecimal *targetCalories = 1.2; // What is the caloric target for one day? The meal plan generator will try to get as close as possible to that goal. (optional)
String *diet = diet_example; // Enter a diet that the meal plan has to adhere to. See a full list of supported diets. (optional)
String *exclude = exclude_example; // A comma-separated list of allergens or ingredients that must be excluded. (optional)

// Generate Meal Plan
[apiInstance generateMealPlanWith:timeFrame
    targetCalories:targetCalories
    diet:diet
    exclude:exclude
              completionHandler: ^(inline_response_200_40 output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var SpoonacularApi = require('spoonacular_api');
var defaultClient = SpoonacularApi.ApiClient.instance;

apiKeyScheme.apiKey = "YOUR API KEY"

//apiKeyScheme.apiKeyPrefix['apiKey'] = "Token"

var api = new SpoonacularApi.MealPlanningApi()
var opts = { 
  'timeFrame': timeFrame_example, // {{String}} Either for one "day" or an entire "week".
  'targetCalories': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} What is the caloric target for one day? The meal plan generator will try to get as close as possible to that goal.
  'diet': diet_example, // {{String}} Enter a diet that the meal plan has to adhere to. See a full list of supported diets.
  'exclude': exclude_example // {{String}} A comma-separated list of allergens or ingredients that must be excluded.
};
var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.generateMealPlan(opts, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class generateMealPlanExample
    {
        public void main()
        {

            // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
            Configuration.Default.ApiKey.Add("apiKey", "YOUR_API_KEY");
            // Uncomment below to setup prefix (e.g. Bearer) for API key, if needed
            // Configuration.Default.ApiKeyPrefix.Add("apiKey", "Bearer");

            var apiInstance = new MealPlanningApi();
            var timeFrame = timeFrame_example;  // String | Either for one "day" or an entire "week". (optional) 
            var targetCalories = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | What is the caloric target for one day? The meal plan generator will try to get as close as possible to that goal. (optional) 
            var diet = diet_example;  // String | Enter a diet that the meal plan has to adhere to. See a full list of supported diets. (optional) 
            var exclude = exclude_example;  // String | A comma-separated list of allergens or ingredients that must be excluded. (optional) 

            try
            {
                // Generate Meal Plan
                inline_response_200_40 result = apiInstance.generateMealPlan(timeFrame, targetCalories, diet, exclude);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling MealPlanningApi.generateMealPlan: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

getMealPlanTemplates

Get Meal Plan Templates

Get meal plan templates from user or public ones.


/mealplanner/{username}/templates

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.MealPlanningApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class MealPlanningApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        MealPlanningApi apiInstance = new MealPlanningApi();
        String username = username_example; // String | The username.
        String hash = hash_example; // String | The private hash for the username.
        try {
            inline_response_200_42 result = apiInstance.getMealPlanTemplates(username, hash);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling MealPlanningApi#getMealPlanTemplates");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

getMealPlanWeek

Get Meal Plan Week

Retrieve a meal planned week for the given user. The username must be a spoonacular user and the hash must the the user's hash that can be found in his/her account.


/mealplanner/{username}/week/{start-date}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"https://api.spoonacular.com/mealplanner/{username}/week/{start-date}?hash="

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        MealPlanningApi apiInstance = new MealPlanningApi();
        String username = username_example; // String | The username.
        String startDate = startDate_example; // String | The start date of the meal planned week in the format yyyy-mm-dd.
        String hash = hash_example; // String | The private hash for the username.
        try {
            inline_response_200_41 result = apiInstance.getMealPlanWeek(username, startDate, hash);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling MealPlanningApi#getMealPlanWeek");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

            System.out.println(result);

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.MenuItemsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class MenuItemsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        MenuItemsApi apiInstance = new MenuItemsApi();
        BigDecimal id = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The menu item id.
        Boolean showOptionalNutrients = true; // Boolean | Whether to show optional nutrients.
        Boolean showZeroValues = true; // Boolean | Whether to show zero values.
        Boolean showIngredients = true; // Boolean | Whether to show a list of ingredients.
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.menuItemNutritionLabelImage(id, showOptionalNutrients, showZeroValues, showIngredients);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling MenuItemsApi#menuItemNutritionLabelImage");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Search Menu Items

Search over 115,000 menu items from over 800 fast food and chain restaurants. For example, McDonald's Big Mac or Starbucks Mocha.

Misc

detectFoodInText

Detect Food in Text

Take any text and find all mentions of food contained within it. This task is also called Named Entity Recognition (NER). In this case, the entities are foods. Either dishes, such as pizza or cheeseburger, or ingredients, such as cucumber or almonds.


/food/detect

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

Conversation Suggests

This endpoint returns suggestions for things the user can say or ask the chatbot.


/food/converse/suggest

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.MiscApi;

import java.util.*;

public class MiscApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        MiscApi apiInstance = new MiscApi();
        String query = query_example; // String | A (partial) query from the user. The endpoint will return if it matches topics it can talk about.
        BigDecimal number = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The number of suggestions to return (between 1 and 25).
        try {
            inline_response_200_61 result = apiInstance.getConversationSuggests(query, number);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling MiscApi#getConversationSuggests");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.MiscApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class MiscApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        MiscApi apiInstance = new MiscApi();
        String query = query_example; // String | The (natural language) search query.
        String type = type_example; // String | The type of the recipes. See a full list of supported meal types.
        String cuisine = cuisine_example; // String | The cuisine(s) of the recipes. One or more, comma separated. See a full list of supported cuisines.
        String diet = diet_example; // String | The diet for which the recipes must be suitable. See a full list of supported diets.
        String includeIngredients = includeIngredients_example; // String | A comma-separated list of ingredients that the recipes should contain.
        String excludeIngredients = excludeIngredients_example; // String | A comma-separated list of ingredients or ingredient types that the recipes must not contain.
        BigDecimal minLength = 1.2; // BigDecimal | Minimum video length in seconds.
        BigDecimal maxLength = 1.2; // BigDecimal | Maximum video length in seconds.
        Integer offset = 56; // Integer | The number of results to skip (between 0 and 900).
        Integer number = 56; // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
        try {
            inline_response_200_57 result = apiInstance.searchFoodVideos(query, type, cuisine, diet, includeIngredients, excludeIngredients, minLength, maxLength, offset, number);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling MiscApi#searchFoodVideos");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

searchSiteContent

Search Site Content

Search spoonacular's site content. You'll be able to find everything that you could also find using the search suggestions on spoonacular.com. This is a suggest API so you can send partial strings as queries.


/food/site/search

talkToChatbot

Talk to Chatbot

This endpoint can be used to have a conversation about food with the spoonacular chatbot. Use the "Get Conversation Suggests" endpoint to show your user what he or she can say.


/food/converse

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        String contextId = contextId_example; // String | An arbitrary globally unique id for your conversation. The conversation can contain states so you should pass your context id if you want the bot to be able to remember the conversation.

            inline_response_200_60 result = apiInstance.talkToChatbot(text, contextId);
            System.out.println(result);

autocompleteProductSearch

Autocomplete Product Search

Generate suggestions for grocery products based on a (partial) query. The matches will be found by looking in the title only.


/food/products/suggest

classifyGroceryProduct

Classify Grocery Product

This endpoint allows you to match a packaged food to a basic category, e.g. a specific brand of milk to the category milk.


/food/products/classify

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ProductsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProductsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        ProductsApi apiInstance = new ProductsApi();
        Products_classify_body body = {
  "value" : {
    "title" : "Kroger Vitamin A & D Reduced Fat 2% Milk",
    "upc" : "",
    "plu_code" : ""
  }
}; // Products_classify_body | 
        String locale = locale_example; // String | The display name of the returned category, supported is en_US (for American English) and en_GB (for British English).
        try {
            inline_response_200_34 result = apiInstance.classifyGroceryProduct(body, locale);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProductsApi#classifyGroceryProduct");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ProductsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProductsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        ProductsApi apiInstance = new ProductsApi();
        BigDecimal id = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The id of the product.
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.productNutritionByIDImage(id);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProductsApi#productNutritionByIDImage");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

                        }];

            // Uncomment below to setup prefix (e.g. Bearer) for API key, if needed
            // Configuration.Default.ApiKeyPrefix.Add("apiKey", "Bearer");

            var apiInstance = new ProductsApi();

productNutritionLabelImage

Product Nutrition Label Image

Get a product's nutrition label as an image.


/food/products/{id}/nutritionLabel.png

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
\
-H "Accept: image/png"\
"https://api.spoonacular.com/food/products/{id}/nutritionLabel.png?showOptionalNutrients=&showZeroValues=&showIngredients="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ProductsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProductsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        ProductsApi apiInstance = new ProductsApi();
        BigDecimal id = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The product id.
        Boolean showOptionalNutrients = true; // Boolean | Whether to show optional nutrients.
        Boolean showZeroValues = true; // Boolean | Whether to show zero values.
        Boolean showIngredients = true; // Boolean | Whether to show a list of ingredients.
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.productNutritionLabelImage(id, showOptionalNutrients, showZeroValues, showIngredients);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProductsApi#productNutritionLabelImage");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

productNutritionLabelWidget

Product Nutrition Label Widget

Get a product's nutrition label as an HTML widget.


/food/products/{id}/nutritionLabel

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
\
-H "Accept: text/html"\
"https://api.spoonacular.com/food/products/{id}/nutritionLabel?defaultCss=&showOptionalNutrients=&showZeroValues=&showIngredients="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ProductsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProductsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        ProductsApi apiInstance = new ProductsApi();
        BigDecimal id = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The product id.
        Boolean defaultCss = true; // Boolean | Whether the default CSS should be added to the response.
        Boolean showOptionalNutrients = true; // Boolean | Whether to show optional nutrients.
        Boolean showZeroValues = true; // Boolean | Whether to show zero values.
        Boolean showIngredients = true; // Boolean | Whether to show a list of ingredients.
        try {
            'String' result = apiInstance.productNutritionLabelWidget(id, defaultCss, showOptionalNutrients, showZeroValues, showIngredients);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProductsApi#productNutritionLabelWidget");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

/food/products/search

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ProductsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProductsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        ProductsApi apiInstance = new ProductsApi();
        String query = query_example; // String | The (natural language) search query.
        BigDecimal minCalories = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of calories the product must have.
        BigDecimal maxCalories = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of calories the product can have.
        BigDecimal minCarbs = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product must have.
        BigDecimal maxCarbs = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product can have.
        BigDecimal minProtein = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of protein in grams the product must have.
        BigDecimal maxProtein = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of protein in grams the product can have.
        BigDecimal minFat = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of fat in grams the product must have.
        BigDecimal maxFat = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of fat in grams the product can have.
        Integer offset = 56; // Integer | The number of results to skip (between 0 and 900).
        Integer number = 56; // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
        try {
            inline_response_200_28 result = apiInstance.searchGroceryProducts(query, minCalories, maxCalories, minCarbs, maxCarbs, minProtein, maxProtein, minFat, maxFat, offset, number);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProductsApi#searchGroceryProducts");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.ProductsApi;

public class ProductsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ProductsApi apiInstance = new ProductsApi();
        String query = query_example; // String | The (natural language) search query.
        BigDecimal minCalories = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of calories the product must have.
        BigDecimal maxCalories = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of calories the product can have.
        BigDecimal minCarbs = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product must have.
        BigDecimal maxCarbs = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product can have.
        BigDecimal minProtein = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of protein in grams the product must have.
        BigDecimal maxProtein = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of protein in grams the product can have.
        BigDecimal minFat = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of fat in grams the product must have.
        BigDecimal maxFat = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of fat in grams the product can have.
        Integer offset = 56; // Integer | The number of results to skip (between 0 and 900).
        Integer number = 56; // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
        try {
            inline_response_200_28 result = apiInstance.searchGroceryProducts(query, minCalories, maxCalories, minCarbs, maxCarbs, minProtein, maxProtein, minFat, maxFat, offset, number);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProductsApi#searchGroceryProducts");

    }

Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];
// Configure API key authorization: (authentication scheme: apiKeyScheme)
[apiConfig setApiKey:@"YOUR_API_KEY" forApiKeyIdentifier:@"apiKey"];
// Uncomment below to setup prefix (e.g. Bearer) for API key, if needed
//[apiConfig setApiKeyPrefix:@"Bearer" forApiKeyIdentifier:@"apiKey"];
String *query = query_example; // The (natural language) search query. (optional)
BigDecimal *minCalories = 1.2; // The minimum amount of calories the product must have. (optional)
BigDecimal *maxCalories = 1.2; // The maximum amount of calories the product can have. (optional)
BigDecimal *minCarbs = 1.2; // The minimum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product must have. (optional)
BigDecimal *maxCarbs = 1.2; // The maximum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product can have. (optional)
BigDecimal *minProtein = 1.2; // The minimum amount of protein in grams the product must have. (optional)
BigDecimal *maxProtein = 1.2; // The maximum amount of protein in grams the product can have. (optional)
BigDecimal *minFat = 1.2; // The minimum amount of fat in grams the product must have. (optional)
BigDecimal *maxFat = 1.2; // The maximum amount of fat in grams the product can have. (optional)
Integer *offset = 56; // The number of results to skip (between 0 and 900). (optional)
Integer *number = 56; // The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10. (optional) (default to 10)

// Search Grocery Products

    minCalories:minCalories
    maxCalories:maxCalories
    minCarbs:minCarbs
    maxCarbs:maxCarbs

    minFat:minFat

var SpoonacularApi = require('spoonacular_api');
var defaultClient = SpoonacularApi.ApiClient.instance;

// Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
var apiKeyScheme = defaultClient.authentications['apiKeyScheme'];
apiKeyScheme.apiKey = "YOUR API KEY"
// Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
//apiKeyScheme.apiKeyPrefix['apiKey'] = "Token"

var api = new SpoonacularApi.ProductsApi()
var opts = { 
  'query': query_example, // {{String}} The (natural language) search query.
  'minCalories': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} The minimum amount of calories the product must have.
  'maxCalories': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} The maximum amount of calories the product can have.
  'minCarbs': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} The minimum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product must have.
  'maxCarbs': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} The maximum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product can have.
  'minProtein': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} The minimum amount of protein in grams the product must have.
  'maxProtein': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} The maximum amount of protein in grams the product can have.
  'minFat': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} The minimum amount of fat in grams the product must have.
  'maxFat': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} The maximum amount of fat in grams the product can have.
  'offset': 56, // {{Integer}} The number of results to skip (between 0 and 900).
  'number': 56 // {{Integer}} The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
};
var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.searchGroceryProducts(opts, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class searchGroceryProductsExample
    {
        public void main()
        {

            // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
            Configuration.Default.ApiKey.Add("apiKey", "YOUR_API_KEY");
            // Uncomment below to setup prefix (e.g. Bearer) for API key, if needed
            // Configuration.Default.ApiKeyPrefix.Add("apiKey", "Bearer");

            var apiInstance = new ProductsApi();
            var query = query_example;  // String | The (natural language) search query. (optional) 
            var minCalories = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of calories the product must have. (optional) 
            var maxCalories = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of calories the product can have. (optional) 
            var minCarbs = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product must have. (optional) 
            var maxCarbs = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product can have. (optional) 
            var minProtein = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of protein in grams the product must have. (optional) 
            var maxProtein = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of protein in grams the product can have. (optional) 
            var minFat = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of fat in grams the product must have. (optional) 
            var maxFat = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of fat in grams the product can have. (optional) 
            var offset = 56;  // Integer | The number of results to skip (between 0 and 900). (optional) 
            var number = 56;  // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10. (optional)  (default to 10)

            try
            {
                // Search Grocery Products
                inline_response_200_28 result = apiInstance.searchGroceryProducts(query, minCalories, maxCalories, minCarbs, maxCarbs, minProtein, maxProtein, minFat, maxFat, offset, number);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ProductsApi.searchGroceryProducts: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

$maxCalories = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of calories the product can have.
$minCarbs = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product must have.
$maxCarbs = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product can have.
$minProtein = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of protein in grams the product must have.
$maxProtein = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of protein in grams the product can have.
$minFat = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of fat in grams the product must have.
$maxFat = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of fat in grams the product can have.
$offset = 56; // Integer | The number of results to skip (between 0 and 900).
$number = 56; // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.

try {
    $result = $api_instance->searchGroceryProducts($query, $minCalories, $maxCalories, $minCarbs, $maxCarbs, $minProtein, $maxProtein, $minFat, $maxFat, $offset, $number);

my $maxCalories = 1.2; # BigDecimal | The maximum amount of calories the product can have.

my $maxCarbs = 1.2; # BigDecimal | The maximum amount of carbohydrates in grams the product can have.
my $minProtein = 1.2; # BigDecimal | The minimum amount of protein in grams the product must have.

Search Grocery Products by UPC

Get information about a packaged food using its UPC.


/food/products/upc/{upc}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ProductsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProductsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        ProductsApi apiInstance = new ProductsApi();
        BigDecimal upc = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The product's UPC.
        try {
            inline_response_200_29 result = apiInstance.searchGroceryProductsByUPC(upc);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProductsApi#searchGroceryProductsByUPC");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

visualizeProductNutritionByID

Product Nutrition by ID Widget

Visualize a product's nutritional information as HTML including CSS.


/food/products/{id}/nutritionWidget

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ProductsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProductsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        ProductsApi apiInstance = new ProductsApi();
        Integer id = 56; // Integer | The item's id.
        Boolean defaultCss = true; // Boolean | Whether the default CSS should be added to the response.
        String accept = accept_example; // String | Accept header.
        try {
            'String' result = apiInstance.visualizeProductNutritionByID(id, defaultCss, accept);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProductsApi#visualizeProductNutritionByID");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

analyzeRecipeInstructions

Analyze Recipe Instructions

This endpoint allows you to break down instructions into atomic steps. Furthermore, each step will contain the ingredients and equipment required. Additionally, all ingredients and equipment from the recipe's instructions will be extracted independently of the step they're used in.


/recipes/analyzeInstructions

import io.swagger.client.auth.*;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        String ingredientName = ingredientName_example; // String | The ingredient which you want to convert.
        BigDecimal sourceAmount = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The amount from which you want to convert, e.g. the 2.5 in "2.5 cups of flour to grams".
        String sourceUnit = sourceUnit_example; // String | The unit from which you want to convert, e.g. the grams in "2.5 cups of flour to grams". You can also use "piece", e.g. "3.4 oz tomatoes to piece"
        String targetUnit = targetUnit_example; // String | The unit to which you want to convert, e.g. the grams in "2.5 cups of flour to grams". You can also use "piece", e.g. "3.4 oz tomatoes to piece"
        try {
            inline_response_200_19 result = apiInstance.convertAmounts(ingredientName, sourceAmount, sourceUnit, targetUnit);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#convertAmounts");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

extractRecipeFromWebsite

Extract Recipe from Website

This endpoint lets you extract recipe data such as title, ingredients, and instructions from any properly formatted Website.


/recipes/extract

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"https://api.spoonacular.com/recipes/extract?url=&forceExtraction=&analyze=&includeNutrition=&includeTaste="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.RecipesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class RecipesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        String url = url_example; // String | The URL of the recipe page.
        Boolean forceExtraction = true; // Boolean | If true, the extraction will be triggered whether we already know the recipe or not. Use this only if information is missing as this operation is slower.
        Boolean analyze = true; // Boolean | If true, the recipe will be analyzed and classified resolving in more data such as cuisines, dish types, and more.
        Boolean includeNutrition = true; // Boolean | Include nutrition data in the recipe information. Nutrition data is per serving. If you want the nutrition data for the entire recipe, just multiply by the number of servings.
        Boolean includeTaste = true; // Boolean | Whether taste data should be added to correctly parsed ingredients.
        try {
            inline_response_200_3 result = apiInstance.extractRecipeFromWebsite(url, forceExtraction, analyze, includeNutrition, includeTaste);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#extractRecipeFromWebsite");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

        Boolean includeNutrition = true; // Boolean | Include nutrition data in the recipe information. Nutrition data is per serving. If you want the nutrition data for the entire recipe, just multiply by the number of servings.
        Boolean includeTaste = true; // Boolean | Whether taste data should be added to correctly parsed ingredients.

  'forceExtraction': true, // {{Boolean}} If true, the extraction will be triggered whether we already know the recipe or not. Use this only if information is missing as this operation is slower.
  'analyze': true, // {{Boolean}} If true, the recipe will be analyzed and classified resolving in more data such as cuisines, dish types, and more.
  'includeNutrition': true, // {{Boolean}} Include nutrition data in the recipe information. Nutrition data is per serving. If you want the nutrition data for the entire recipe, just multiply by the number of servings.
  'includeTaste': true // {{Boolean}} Whether taste data should be added to correctly parsed ingredients.
};
var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.extractRecipeFromWebsite(url, opts, callback);

getAnalyzedRecipeInstructions

Get Analyzed Recipe Instructions

Get an analyzed breakdown of a recipe's instructions. Each step is enriched with the ingredients and equipment required.


/recipes/{id}/analyzedInstructions

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        Integer id = 56; // Integer | The item's id.
        Boolean stepBreakdown = true; // Boolean | Whether to break down the recipe steps even more.
        try {
            inline_response_200_13 result = apiInstance.getAnalyzedRecipeInstructions(id, stepBreakdown);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#getAnalyzedRecipeInstructions");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

getRandomRecipes

Get Random Recipes

Find random (popular) recipes. If you need to filter recipes by diet, nutrition etc. you might want to consider using the complex recipe search endpoint and set the sort request parameter to random.


/recipes/random

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

\

"https://api.spoonacular.com/recipes/random?limitLicense=&tags=&number="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.RecipesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class RecipesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        Boolean limitLicense = true; // Boolean | Whether the recipes should have an open license that allows display with proper attribution.
        String tags = tags_example; // String | The tags (can be diets, meal types, cuisines, or intolerances) that the recipe must have.
        Integer number = 56; // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
        try {
            inline_response_200_6 result = apiInstance.getRandomRecipes(limitLicense, tags, number);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#getRandomRecipes");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Get Recipe Information

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.RecipesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class RecipesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        Integer id = 56; // Integer | The item's id.
        Boolean includeNutrition = true; // Boolean | Include nutrition data in the recipe information. Nutrition data is per serving. If you want the nutrition data for the entire recipe, just multiply by the number of servings.
        try {
            inline_response_200_3 result = apiInstance.getRecipeInformation(id, includeNutrition);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#getRecipeInformation");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

getRecipeInformationBulk

Get Recipe Information Bulk

Get information about multiple recipes at once. This is equivalent to calling the Get Recipe Information endpoint multiple times, but faster.


/recipes/informationBulk

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.RecipesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class RecipesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        String ids = ids_example; // String | A comma-separated list of recipe ids.
        Boolean includeNutrition = true; // Boolean | Include nutrition data in the recipe information. Nutrition data is per serving. If you want the nutrition data for the entire recipe, just multiply by the number of servings.
        try {
            array[inline_response_200_4] result = apiInstance.getRecipeInformationBulk(ids, includeNutrition);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#getRecipeInformationBulk");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)

recipeNutritionLabelImage

Recipe Nutrition Label Image

Get a recipe's nutrition label as an image.


/recipes/{id}/nutritionLabel.png

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript

\
-H "Accept: image/png"\

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.RecipesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class RecipesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        BigDecimal id = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The recipe id.
        Boolean showOptionalNutrients = true; // Boolean | Whether to show optional nutrients.
        Boolean showZeroValues = true; // Boolean | Whether to show zero values.
        Boolean showIngredients = true; // Boolean | Whether to show a list of ingredients.
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.recipeNutritionLabelImage(id, showOptionalNutrients, showZeroValues, showIngredients);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#recipeNutritionLabelImage");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

recipeTasteByIDImage

Recipe Taste by ID Image

Get a recipe's taste as an image. The tastes supported are sweet, salty, sour, bitter, savory, and fatty.


/recipes/{id}/tasteWidget.png

import java.util.*;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        BigDecimal id = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The recipe id.
        Boolean normalize = true; // Boolean | Normalize to the strongest taste.
        String rgb = rgb_example; // String | Red, green, blue values for the chart color.
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.recipeTasteByIDImage(id, normalize, rgb);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#recipeTasteByIDImage");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

searchRecipes

Search Recipes

Search through hundreds of thousands of recipes using advanced filtering and ranking. NOTE: This method combines searching by query, by ingredients, and by nutrients into one endpoint.


/recipes/complexSearch

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"https://api.spoonacular.com/recipes/complexSearch?query=&cuisine=&excludeCuisine=&diet=&intolerances=&equipment=&includeIngredients=&excludeIngredients=&type=&instructionsRequired=&fillIngredients=&addRecipeInformation=&addRecipeNutrition=&author=&tags=&recipeBoxId=&titleMatch=&maxReadyTime=&ignorePantry=&sort=&sortDirection=&minCarbs=&maxCarbs=&minProtein=&maxProtein=&minCalories=&maxCalories=&minFat=&maxFat=&minAlcohol=&maxAlcohol=&minCaffeine=&maxCaffeine=&minCopper=&maxCopper=&minCalcium=&maxCalcium=&minCholine=&maxCholine=&minCholesterol=&maxCholesterol=&minFluoride=&maxFluoride=&minSaturatedFat=&maxSaturatedFat=&minVitaminA=&maxVitaminA=&minVitaminC=&maxVitaminC=&minVitaminD=&maxVitaminD=&minVitaminE=&maxVitaminE=&minVitaminK=&maxVitaminK=&minVitaminB1=&maxVitaminB1=&minVitaminB2=&maxVitaminB2=&minVitaminB5=&maxVitaminB5=&minVitaminB3=&maxVitaminB3=&minVitaminB6=&maxVitaminB6=&minVitaminB12=&maxVitaminB12=&minFiber=&maxFiber=&minFolate=&maxFolate=&minFolicAcid=&maxFolicAcid=&minIodine=&maxIodine=&minIron=&maxIron=&minMagnesium=&maxMagnesium=&minManganese=&maxManganese=&minPhosphorus=&maxPhosphorus=&minPotassium=&maxPotassium=&minSelenium=&maxSelenium=&minSodium=&maxSodium=&minSugar=&maxSugar=&minZinc=&maxZinc=&offset=&number=&limitLicense="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.RecipesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class RecipesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        String query = query_example; // String | The (natural language) search query.
        String cuisine = cuisine_example; // String | The cuisine(s) of the recipes. One or more, comma separated (will be interpreted as 'OR'). See a full list of supported cuisines.
        String excludeCuisine = excludeCuisine_example; // String | The cuisine(s) the recipes must not match. One or more, comma separated (will be interpreted as 'AND'). See a full list of supported cuisines.
        String diet = diet_example; // String | The diet for which the recipes must be suitable. See a full list of supported diets.
        String intolerances = intolerances_example; // String | A comma-separated list of intolerances. All recipes returned must not contain ingredients that are not suitable for people with the intolerances entered. See a full list of supported intolerances.
        String equipment = equipment_example; // String | The equipment required. Multiple values will be interpreted as 'or'. For example, value could be "blender, frying pan, bowl".
        String includeIngredients = includeIngredients_example; // String | A comma-separated list of ingredients that should/must be used in the recipes.
        String excludeIngredients = excludeIngredients_example; // String | A comma-separated list of ingredients or ingredient types that the recipes must not contain.
        String type = type_example; // String | The type of recipe. See a full list of supported meal types.
        Boolean instructionsRequired = true; // Boolean | Whether the recipes must have instructions.
        Boolean fillIngredients = true; // Boolean | Add information about the ingredients and whether they are used or missing in relation to the query.
        Boolean addRecipeInformation = true; // Boolean | If set to true, you get more information about the recipes returned.
        Boolean addRecipeNutrition = true; // Boolean | If set to true, you get nutritional information about each recipes returned.
        String author = author_example; // String | The username of the recipe author.
        String tags = tags_example; // String | The tags (can be diets, meal types, cuisines, or intolerances) that the recipe must have.
        BigDecimal recipeBoxId = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The id of the recipe box to which the search should be limited to.
        String titleMatch = titleMatch_example; // String | Enter text that must be found in the title of the recipes.
        BigDecimal maxReadyTime = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum time in minutes it should take to prepare and cook the recipe.
        Boolean ignorePantry = true; // Boolean | Whether to ignore typical pantry items, such as water, salt, flour, etc.
        String sort = sort_example; // String | The strategy to sort recipes by. See a full list of supported sorting options.
        String sortDirection = sortDirection_example; // String | The direction in which to sort. Must be either 'asc' (ascending) or 'desc' (descending).
        BigDecimal minCarbs = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of carbohydrates in grams the recipe must have.
        BigDecimal maxCarbs = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of carbohydrates in grams the recipe can have.
        BigDecimal minProtein = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of protein in grams the recipe must have.
        BigDecimal maxProtein = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of protein in grams the recipe can have.
        BigDecimal minCalories = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of calories the recipe must have.
        BigDecimal maxCalories = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of calories the recipe can have.
        BigDecimal minFat = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of fat in grams the recipe must have.
        BigDecimal maxFat = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of fat in grams the recipe can have.
        BigDecimal minAlcohol = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The minimum amount of alcohol in grams the recipe must have.
        BigDecimal maxAlcohol = 1.2; // BigDecimal | The maximum amount of alcohol in grams the recipe can have.

import io.swagger.client.api.RecipesApi;

public class RecipesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        String query = query_example; // String | The (natural language) search query.
        String cuisine = cuisine_example; // String | The cuisine(s) of the recipes. One or more, comma separated (will be interpreted as 'OR'). See a full list of supported cuisines.
        String excludeCuisine = excludeCuisine_example; // String | The cuisine(s) the recipes must not match. One or more, comma separated (will be interpreted as 'AND'). See a full list of supported cuisines.
        String diet = diet_example; // String | The diet for which the recipes must be suitable. See a full list of supported diets.
        String intolerances = intolerances_example; // String | A comma-separated list of intolerances. All recipes returned must not contain ingredients that are not suitable for people with the intolerances entered. See a full list of supported intolerances.
        String equipment = equipment_example; // String | The equipment required. Multiple values will be interpreted as 'or'. For example, value could be "blender, frying pan, bowl".
        String includeIngredients = includeIngredients_example; // String | A comma-separated list of ingredients that should/must be used in the recipes.
        String excludeIngredients = excludeIngredients_example; // String | A comma-separated list of ingredients or ingredient types that the recipes must not contain.
        String type = type_example; // String | The type of recipe. See a full list of supported meal types.
        Boolean instructionsRequired = true; // Boolean | Whether the recipes must have instructions.
        Boolean fillIngredients = true; // Boolean | Add information about the ingredients and whether they are used or missing in relation to the query.
        Boolean addRecipeInformation = true; // Boolean | If set to true, you get more information about the recipes returned.
        Boolean addRecipeNutrition = true; // Boolean | If set to true, you get nutritional information about each recipes returned.

searchRecipesByIngredients

Search Recipes by Ingredients

Ever wondered what recipes you can cook with the ingredients you have in your fridge or pantry? This endpoint lets you find recipes that either maximize the usage of ingredients you have at hand (pre shopping) or minimize the ingredients that you don't currently have (post shopping). 


/recipes/findByIngredients

        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        String ingredients = ingredients_example; // String | A comma-separated list of ingredients that the recipes should contain.
        Integer number = 56; // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
        Boolean limitLicense = true; // Boolean | Whether the recipes should have an open license that allows display with proper attribution.
        BigDecimal ranking = 1.2; // BigDecimal | Whether to maximize used ingredients (1) or minimize missing ingredients (2) first.
        Boolean ignorePantry = true; // Boolean | Whether to ignore typical pantry items, such as water, salt, flour, etc.
        try {
            array[inline_response_200_1] result = apiInstance.searchRecipesByIngredients(ingredients, number, limitLicense, ranking, ignorePantry);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#searchRecipesByIngredients");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

var SpoonacularApi = require('spoonacular_api');
var defaultClient = SpoonacularApi.ApiClient.instance;

// Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
var apiKeyScheme = defaultClient.authentications['apiKeyScheme'];
apiKeyScheme.apiKey = "YOUR API KEY"
// Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
//apiKeyScheme.apiKeyPrefix['apiKey'] = "Token"

var api = new SpoonacularApi.RecipesApi()
var opts = { 
  'ingredients': ingredients_example, // {{String}} A comma-separated list of ingredients that the recipes should contain.
  'number': 56, // {{Integer}} The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10.
  'limitLicense': true, // {{Boolean}} Whether the recipes should have an open license that allows display with proper attribution.
  'ranking': 1.2, // {{BigDecimal}} Whether to maximize used ingredients (1) or minimize missing ingredients (2) first.
  'ignorePantry': true // {{Boolean}} Whether to ignore typical pantry items, such as water, salt, flour, etc.
};
var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.searchRecipesByIngredients(opts, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class searchRecipesByIngredientsExample
    {
        public void main()
        {

            // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
            Configuration.Default.ApiKey.Add("apiKey", "YOUR_API_KEY");
            // Uncomment below to setup prefix (e.g. Bearer) for API key, if needed
            // Configuration.Default.ApiKeyPrefix.Add("apiKey", "Bearer");

            var apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
            var ingredients = ingredients_example;  // String | A comma-separated list of ingredients that the recipes should contain. (optional) 
            var number = 56;  // Integer | The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10. (optional)  (default to 10)
            var limitLicense = true;  // Boolean | Whether the recipes should have an open license that allows display with proper attribution. (optional)  (default to true)
            var ranking = 1.2;  // BigDecimal | Whether to maximize used ingredients (1) or minimize missing ingredients (2) first. (optional) 
            var ignorePantry = true;  // Boolean | Whether to ignore typical pantry items, such as water, salt, flour, etc. (optional)  (default to false)

            try
            {
                // Search Recipes by Ingredients
                array[inline_response_200_1] result = apiInstance.searchRecipesByIngredients(ingredients, number, limitLicense, ranking, ignorePantry);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling RecipesApi.searchRecipesByIngredients: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

searchRecipesByNutrients

Search Recipes by Nutrients

Find a set of recipes that adhere to the given nutritional limits. You may set limits for macronutrients (calories, protein, fat, and carbohydrate) and/or many micronutrients.


/recipes/findByNutrients

        // Configure API key authorization: apiKeyScheme
        ApiKeyAuth apiKeyScheme = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("apiKeyScheme");
        apiKeyScheme.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //apiKeyScheme.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        RecipesApi apiInstance = new RecipesApi();
        Integer id = 56; // Integer | The item's id.
        try {
            inline_response_200_14 result = apiInstance.summarizeRecipe(id);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling RecipesApi#summarizeRecipe");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

};

  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {

  }
};
api.visualizeRecipeIngredientsByID(id, opts, callback);

  }
